liability /ˌlaɪəˈbɪlɪtɪ/

(liabilities) 

1. N-COUNT If you say that someone or something is a liability , you mean that they cause a lot of problems or embarrassment. 累赘 

例： As the president's prestige continues to fall, they're clearly beginning to consider him a liability. 随着总统的威信持续下降，他们显然开始认为他是一个累赘。 

2. N-COUNT A company's or organization's liabilities are the sums of money which it owes. 负债 [商业] 

例： The company had assets of $138 million and liabilities of $120.5 million. 该公司有1.38亿美元资产和1.205亿美元的负债。 

3.  →  see also liable

